Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is light-brown in section, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and remains of two lines of black-painted Greek text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393814) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393814)
